02:33:16,626 --> 02:33:19,626
My Shiva is the son
of such a great king!

965
02:33:20,751 --> 02:33:23,459
We are so glad
to hear about him.

966
02:33:24,418 --> 02:33:27,626
I wish we can
see the great man once!

967
02:33:30,168 --> 02:33:31,584
He is no more.

968
02:33:33,293 --> 02:33:35,126
The saviour is no more!
(That God is no more!)

969
02:33:42,418 --> 02:33:44,626
You said no enemy
could come near him.

970
02:33:45,126 --> 02:33:47,376
You said the weapons
were afraid to touch him?

971
02:33:48,918 --> 02:33:51,001
How did such
a great warrior die?

972
02:33:52,918 --> 02:33:56,459
More grievous than
the wound of a sword or a spear

973
02:33:57,376 --> 02:33:59,126
is a stab in the back, Mahendra.

974
02:33:59,543 --> 02:34:02,251
Who? Who was it?

975
02:34:05,501 --> 02:34:06,876
That traitor...

976
02:34:09,126 --> 02:34:10,334
was me!

977
02:34:27,543 --> 02:34:38,501
"Golden dreams
and great heartache."

978
02:34:41,376 --> 02:34:51,501
"churn in the depth of the soul
of this river called life."

979
02:34:52,918 --> 02:35:02,834
"When great mountains
lay in its path."

980
02:35:04,626 --> 02:35:15,876
"it cuts deep gorges through
the rock to keep flowing!"

981
02:35:17,168 --> 02:35:33,376
"This unstoppable, inexhaustible
river called life."

982
02:35:35,126 --> 02:35:41,626
"it is called
the river of life."

